# Firebase web client configuration.
#
# These are NOT secrets — Firebase ships them to the browser by design and they
# end up in the built JS bundle. Your real protection is Firestore Security
# Rules + Firebase Auth + the Authorized Domains list. Still, we keep the values
# out of source control so the repo stays generic and easy to rotate.
#
# 1. Copy this file to ".env" (which is git-ignored).
# 2. Fill in the values from your Firebase project:
#    Firebase Console > Project settings > General > "Your apps" (Web app).
# 3. For the deployed site, add the same values as GitHub Actions secrets
#    (see README "Deploy" section).

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
